                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>During his press conference of November 30, President Truman commented on the
                    question of use of the atomic bomb in the Korean conflict. His remarks on the
                    subject appear in footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_115">page 115</ref>. For
                    documentation on the issue of employment of nuclear weapons in the Korean War,
                    see <ref target="frus1950v07">volume VII</ref>. See in particular the memorandum
                    for the record by Ambassador at Large Philip C. Jessup, December 7, of the
                    conversation that day between President Truman and Prime <pb facs="0607" n="591"
                        xml:id="pg_591"/> Minister Attlee concerning use of the atomic bomb, and the
                    annex thereto, <ref target="frus1950v07#pg_1435">volume VII, page
                    1435</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
